<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Inline Assessment MathML 1.4//EN" "http://oli.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_inline_assessment_mathml_1_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="pancreas_islets_digt"><title>tutor</title><page><question id="q1"><body>Which of the following correctly describes the pancreatic islets?</body><multiple_choice select="single" shuffle="true"><choice value="A">They contain exocrine cells.</choice><choice value="B">They contain 99% of the cells</choice><choice value="C">They produce hormones</choice><choice value="D">They are also called acini cells</choice></multiple_choice><part id="c5cc99e387454526be909ad00507ff06"><skillref idref="pancreas_islets_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. They contain endocrine cells.</feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. Only 1% of the cells of the pancreas are located in the islets.</feedback></response><response match="C" score="10"><feedback>Correct. They do produce hormones such as insulin and glucagon.</feedback></response><response match="D" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. The alternate name for the islets are the islets of Langerhans. Acini cells are exocrine cells.</feedback></response></part></question></page></assessment>
